entry.title: Replace ExecuteScript with ExecJs
entry.content:
ExecuteScript is deprecated in favor of ExecJs. ExecJs is more

flexible and has better error-handling. If the script's completion

value is *not* a Promise, then ExecJs is a drop-in replacement for

ExecuteScript. Otherwise, the new equivalent is to use ExecJs with the

EXECUTE_SCRIPT_NO_RESOLVE_PROMISES option.



This CL was uploaded by git cl split.

entry.title: [SuperSize] Viewer: Add Metadata Tree with tables for leaf data.
entry.content:
This CL changes the metadata view (of top-level |metadata|) from JSON

dump of {size_file, before_size_file} fields to the Metadata Tree view:

* Show only selected fields: |build_config| if available, and |metadata|

fields under each container.

* Below top-level "Metadata", show containers as groups, and render

|metadata| beneath as tables.

* For diff mode, merge "before" and "load" data in groups and tables.



Details:

* viewer.html: Rename #div-metrics-icons to #div-misc-icons; add

#metadataicon; add #tmpl-metadata-tree-{group,leaf}; change

#div-metadata-view content to support tree.

* state.js: Add getMetadataIconTemplate(); adapt to rename from

"metric icons" to "misc icons".

* ui-base.js: Extract getOrMakeContainers() from MetricsTreeModel.

* Add metadata-tree-ui.js:

* Add classes {MetadataTreeModel, MetadataTreeUi}, which are similar

to the Metrics Tree counterparts.

* MetadataTreeModel: Extract desired portions top-level metadata (and

in particular, ignoring metrics_by_file and section_size) to create

intermediate tree of MetadataTreeNode whose leaves consists of lists

of MetadataItem.

* MetadataTreeUi: Performs dynamic tree and table rendering.

* ui-main.js:

* Store MetadataTreeModel and MetadataTreeUi instances.

* Pivot renderMetadata() into preprocessSizeFileInPlace().

* Replace legacy setMetadataContent() with new code

renderAndShowMetadataTree().

entry.title: Specify overlay damage in pixels in viewport space
entry.content:
Currently we are doing a bunch of math to convert damage into buffer

space, and then we're undoing most of that math to convert back to

surface space before passing it to Wayland.



This doesn't really make sense because Exo doesn't even support the

buffer space damage API. It's also an opportunity for floating point

errors to occur. And the work is ultimately unnecessary because damage

in Ash is only useful in pixel coordinates.



There are also some existing bugs in the math when dealing with solid

color overlays which don't really have a buffer space to begin with.

Fixing this bug will allow us to specify most damage on the root

surface, which is technically a solid color overlay.

entry.content:

current context, but that's not always possible when destroying

this case, it's easier to simply not cache the GL textures and instead

create them on the fly like we do for D3DImageBackings used for WebGPU.

entry.title: [wayland] Cancel dnd when drag target or dragged window destroyed
entry.content:
This CL updates the WaylandWindowDragController to cancel the dnd

session client-side when either of the drag target window or the

dragged window are destroyed.



The dnd session is not cancelled when either the pointer grab or

origin window are destroyed as this occurrence is already supported

and defined by the dnd code.



The client terminates the dnd session by calling OnDataSourceFinish()

which resets the wl_data_source and performs some client-side

cleanup. The spec indicates that the destruction of the data source

can be performed to cancel the dnd session.



To handle any possible events sent by the server, but not yet

received by the client after the dnd session has been cancelled, the

client will no-op any further dnd events after this has occurred.

entry.title: inputs: Introduce ExtendSelectionAndReplace/ReplaceSurroundingText API.
entry.content:
ChromeOS has a common operation of "replace some existing text around

the cursor with some new text". This is used in autocorrection, grammar

check, longpress diacritics etc.



This is currently accomplished by doing ExtendSelectionAndDelete (aka

DeleteSurroundingText), followed by a InsertText (aka CommitText).

There are two problems with this:



1) Because it's not atomic, users may see a brief flash.



2) Some websites do not support ExtendSelectionAndDelete correctly.



Introduce a new ExtendSelectionAndReplace/ReplaceSurroundingText API

that can be used by longpress diacritics on ChromeOS. Blink already

supports this operation for Mac, and we can fallback to the two

separate operations for other clients.

entry.title: [CrOS Cellular] Prevent cyclical shill calls to SetProperties().
entry.content:
Previously, we continuously sent revamp APNs to shill in ApnMigrator's

NetworkListChanged() when the flag is on, causing NetworkListChanged()

to be triggered recursively with each update to shill.



This CL adds a stopping condition where if the cellular network has

already been updated with the revamped APN list in shill, ApnMigrator

will no longer tell shill to update the network with the revamp

ApnList.



Note that each time the flag is flipped on, the set that keeps track

of the networks that APNs have already been sent to in shill will clear

because ApnMigrator will be constructed each time the flag is enabled

or disabled.



Fixed: b/280886640

Test: manual and unittest *ApnMigrator*

entry.title: [Extensions] Fix side panel icon not showing up for certain displays
entry.content:
The reason why this happens is because different display request

different scale factors for the extension's icon (i.e. 27 inch external

monitor requests 1x, and a Macbook pro 16 inch screen requests 2x).



If the representation for a requested scale factor is not found at

paint time, then it is requested when an action (i.e. mouseover, or

or repainting) is taken.



The solution involves loading all supported scale factors upfront.

Also, since the extension's side panel icon will always point to the

same image skia, the `OnExtensionIconImageChanged` call was not

necessary (doesn't seem to affect tests either).

which caused (not being called in time) some issues in the past.

being returned by `base::i18n::GetConfiguredLocale()`.

determined during `ui::ResourceBundle::LoadLocaleResources` [2].

`l10n_utils` is eventually used in CountryNamesForLocale [3]

entry.title: Replace ExecuteScript with ExecJs
entry.content:
ExecuteScript is deprecated in favor of ExecJs. ExecJs is more

flexible and has better error-handling. If the script's completion

value is *not* a Promise, then ExecJs is a drop-in replacement for

ExecuteScript. Otherwise, the new equivalent is to use ExecJs with the

EXECUTE_SCRIPT_NO_RESOLVE_PROMISES option.

entry.title: [ImmersiveFullscreenMac] fix overlay window placement on macOS 10.15
entry.content:
When the toolbar is hidden the overlay windows were not hidden when

running on macOS 10.15.



This CL properly hides the overlay windows when the toolbar is hidden.



macOS 10.15 does not call `OnTitlebarFrameDidChange` as often as newer

versions of macOS. This is due to the way 10.15 animates the

NSTitlebarAccessoryViewController. Instead of moving the NSView within

the NSWindow (as is done in macOS 10.15+), the entire NSWindow moves.

To accommodate this difference, extra calls to

`LayoutWindowWithAnchorView` are added to the tab overlay window.
